To conduct the electrochemical measurements, an IviumStat potentiostat was used with graphite rod, Ag|AgCl (KCl-saturated) and carbon cloth as counter, reference and working electrode, respectively. All electrochemical experiments were performed in a H-cell at ambient temperature. Nafion membrane-117 proton exchange membrane was used to separate the anodic and cathodic compartments of H Cell. The electrochemical activity of catalyst was measured using a 3-electrode system where CoTe-modified carbon cloth was used as the working electrode. The Ag|AgCl reference electrode was calibrated with a Pt wire in H2-saturated H2SO4 and an open circuit potential was obtained as − 0.199 V. The potential reported vs Ag|AgCl was changed to reversible hydrogen electrode (RHE) using the following equation:1ERHE=EAg|AgCl+0.059pH+EAg|AgCl0\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
